    "Chronoframe" : {
      "comment" : "The name of the app",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Chronoframe is a darkroom for time. Point it at a folder of photos and videos and it organizes a clean, dated copy at your destination — never moving, never overwriting your originals." : {
      "comment" : "A description of the functionality of Chronoframe.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Chronoframe is a native macOS app built with Swift, SwiftUI, AppKit, Vision, Quick Look, and SQLite." : {
      "comment" : "A description of Chronoframe.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Chronoframe operates inside a secure OS-level sandbox. It only accesses the specific folders you explicitly select." : {
      "comment" : "A description of how Chronoframe operates.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Chronoframe will move every recognised file in the destination into the %@ layout. Originals are not deleted, but files will appear at new paths. Open the Run workspace to track progress." : {
      "comment" : "A message in a confirmation dialog that asks the user to reorganize their destination.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
